Based on the web page content, here's a minimal flake.nix example for uv2nix:

```nix
{
  inputs = {
    uv2nix.url = "github:pyproject-nix/uv2nix";
    nixpkgs.url = "nixpkgs";
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, uv2nix }: 
    let 
      system = "x86_64-linux";  # adjust as needed
      pkgs = nixpkgs.legacyPackages.${system};
    in {
      devShell.${system} = pkgs.mkShell {
        buildInputs = [ 
          uv2nix.packages.${system}.default 
        ];
      };
    };
}
```

This example demonstrates integrating uv2nix as a Nix flake input, based on the introduction which describes uv2nix as a tool for "generating Nix derivations dynamically using pure Nix code" for Python workspaces.

